@Node "Purpose" "Purpose of CyberView"

At the WoC 1994 in Cologne I had a nice talk with Frank Mariak one of the
authors of CyBERgraphics about their plans to write a hardware independent
Workbench Emulation which should add 24bit support to Intuition.

Because Commodore probably will never provide a operating system with RTG
I liked the idea of a new standard and decided to support it by writing an
image viewer for CyBERgraphics.

This program called "CyberView" is the result of this effort.
@EndNode

@Node "Features" "Features of CyberView"

CyberView will run on any Amiga with OS 3.0 (or newer) and an installed
CyBERgraphics system. The amount of free memory which is required depends
on the size of the images which shall be viewed. CyberView can be used from
@{"CLI" link "CLI"} and @{"Workbench" link "Workbench"}.

Supported file formats are:

- @{b}GIF@{ub}

- @{b}IFF ILBM@{ub}
  (1-8 bitplanes, EHB, HAM, HAM8, 24bit)

- @{b}JFIF@{ub}
  (based in part on the work of the Independent JPEG Group)

- @{b}DataTypes@{ub}

- @{b}PBM+@{ub}
  (formats P1-P6)

- @{b}IFF PBM@{ub}
  (only 8 bitplanes, no masking data)

- @{b}PCX@{ub}
  (monochrom, EGA 1-4 bitplanes, VGA, 24bit)
@EndNode

@Node "CLI" "Using CyberView from CLI"

@{b}SYNOPSIS@{ub}
	CyberView FILES/M,DELAY/N,CENTER/S,WIDTH/K/N/,HEIGHT/K/N,INFO/S

@{b}ARGUMENTS@{ub}
	FILES:		filename(s) or AmigaDOS pattern(s) of the image(s)
			which shall be viewed

	DELAY:		automatically end viewing the current picture after
			the supplied number of seconds

	CENTER:		center picture on screen

	WIDTH:		width of the screen

	HEIGHT:		height of the screen

	INFO:		view informations about the builtin loaders

@{b}EXAMPLES@{ub}
	Open a file requester to select a picture:
	 CyberView

	Load a single picture:
	 CyberView Awakening.JPG

	Load all pictures ending with ".ILBM", go to the next picture
	after 10 seconds:
	 CyberView #?.ILBM DELAY 10

	Load "One.GIF" and "Two.PBM" and show them on a 320x240 screen:
	 CyberView One.GIF Two.PBM WIDTH 320 HEIGHT 240

	Show informations about the builtin loaders:
	 CyberView INFO
@EndNode

@Node "Workbench" "Using CyberView from Workbench"

There are two ways of using CyberView from the Workbench:

1.) @{b}As Default Tool@{ub}:
    Specify CyberView as the default tool of an image icon.
    Then double click on the image icon to view the picture.

2.) @{b}Multi Selection@{ub}:
    You can also use Workbench's multi selection feature to view
    pictures using CyberView. Click (single click) on an image
    icon, then press the shift key on your keyboard and continue
    to single click as many image icons as you wish.
    When you're done double click on the CyberView program icon
    (while still holding the shift key).
@EndNode

@Node "Display" "Controlling CyberView's display"

While CyberView is loading a picture you can use @{b}SPACE@{ub}, @{b}RETURN@{ub} or any
mouse button to skip to the next picture. If you press @{b}ESC@{ub} or @{b}CTRL-C@{ub}
CyberView will be terminated.

After the picture has been loaded you can use @{b}ESC@{ub} or @{b}CTRL-C@{ub} to end
CyberView. If you press a mouse button or any other key the next picture
will be loaded.

CyberView uses autoscroll screens for oversized pictures. So you can
scroll the picture by moving the mouse arround.
@EndNode

@Node "Future" "Some ideas for the future of CyberView"

These features @{b}might@{ub} be added to future versions of CyberView:

- add support for more file formats
- get arguments "WIDTH", "HEIGHT" and "DELAY" from icon's tooltypes
  if CyberView is started from the Workbench
@EndNode

@Node "History" "Developement of CyberView"

CyberView 1.0:
- first public release
- loaders: ILBM 1.0, JFIF 1.0, DataTypes 1.0

GIF 1.0
- Because CompuServe is said not to ask for payment for freeware I decided
  to risk to release the GIF loader.

DataTypes 1.1:
- The image data is no longer copied but directly used if possible. This
  saves both memory and time.

CyberView 1.1:
- loaders: ILBM 1.0, JFIF 1.0, DataTypes 1.1, GIF 1.0
- added "DELAY/N" argument

PBM 1.0:
- new loader for PBM+ files

CyberView 1.2:
- loaders: ILBM 1.0, JFIF 1.0, DataTypes 1.1, GIF 1.0, PBM 1.0
- CyberView can now be aborted by pressing CTRL-C even if the progress
  window was not opened.
- some small improvements

GIF 2.0:
- adjusted to CyberView 2.0

JFIF 2.0:
- new loader based in part on the work of the Independent JPEG Group

IFF 1.0:
- replaces the old ILBM loader, supports IFF-ILBM and IFF-PBM

PBM 2.0:
- adjusted to CyberView 2.0

DataTypes 2.0:
- adjusted to CyberView 2.0

PCX 1.0:
- new loader for PCX files

CyberView 2.0:
- major rewrite:
  Image data is now read line by line and transfered to the screen
  immediately. This saves not only memory, you can also look at the
  picture while it is loaded.
- loaders: GIF 2.0, ILBM 1.0, JFIF 2.0, PBM 2.0, DataTypes 2.0, PCX 1.0
- improved buffered I/O (PBM loader now twice as fast)
- new @{"command line arguments" link "CLI"}
- can be made resident
- opens a file requester if no filename is supplied

CyberView 2.1:
- opens a file requester if started from Workbench without arguments
- some small improvements
@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "Installation of CyberView"

To install "CyberView" you only have to copy the binary and its icon to
any directory you like.

Users of my directory utility Filer (version 3.20 or newer) can add these
lines to their configuration file to use CyberView:
 CLASS "#?","FORM????ILBM","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?","FORM????PBM ","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?","??????JFIF","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?","GIF8","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?","P1","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?","P2","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?","P3","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?","P4","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?","P5","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?","P6","CyberView %s CENTER"
 CLASS "#?.PCX","","CyberView %s CENTER"
@EndNode

